  "text": "The proposed approach was applied for prediction of new interactions in protein phosphorylation networks. The interaction cascades between protein kinases and their substrates play a key role in cell cycle regulation, in the normal and tumor cells [CITATION_1] . Protein phosphorylation (including substrate specificity of different protein kinase types, phosphorylated peptides and regions responsible for kinase-substrate binding) is well studied, providing a lot of information necessary for the evaluation and improvement of the method. The proteins included into the training set were classified according to the kinase's specificity, so that each class consisted of the proteins phosphorylated by the same kinase.",
